"No. She told us that she will oppose us."

Petr Vectern

"I hope Lucian managed to talk some sense into him."

"Maybe you shouldn't have pushed the Court so much... Taking away their immunity was a bit too aggressive."

Petr Vectern

"I wouldn't blame them if they vote no."

Player

"I agree. We have to watch him closely."

Paskal Beniwoll

"Mr. Kibener aside, we seem to be in a very troubling situation regardless."

Petr Vectern

"And we've got enough trouble aside from him."

Livia Suno

"He's obviously trying to send you a message, but--"

Player

"Yeah. A picture of Tarquin Soll. What a nice present..."

Player

"This must be some kind of a message."

Petr Vectern

"I really want to believe in that..."

Lucian Galade

"You must also start preparing a speech to announce the changes, sir."

Player

"What do you think this means, Livia?"

Player

"Did Orso say anything to you about this?"

Livia Suno

"Mr. Vice President. I'll be leaving now."
